The paper discusses the functional make-up of spreadsheets and how it can assist researchers in targeting particular structures in spreadsheet software for further investigation. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of spreadsheets for decision support systems, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper suggests the value of Example Driven Modelling, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY).
